Text.string: Got the space of a spit to help me with a heap of deadbeats?

I'm a baker by trade. Started making a pretty penny catering bandit birthday bashes—I ain't no bandit, but a girl's gotta get paid somehow. Now, I got these deadbeats who thought they could get away with not payin' for my delectable delights. So I'm lookin' to make an example of them. Grab me a dozen spider-ant eggs and a barrel of gunpowder. I'll warm up the oven!

I tried to be a regular baker, but there just ain't enough regular people around here to make a livin'. So I started caterin' to these bandit looneybins. Most of 'em haven't even tasted somethin' sweet in their whole lives—until they sample some of my goods.
Now pull the lever and shoot them targets to see if you can get a barrel outta that bad boy.
This'll only take a tick. And while I finish up the cake, why don't you go around back and fetch me some candles. And by “candles”, I mean “sticks of dynamite”.
Look at this ugly ol' beauty! Now pick up them cake layers and we'll get this vengeful show on the road!
Go ahead and assemble the cake on that minecart!
Private party, chopbait. Whaddya want?!
There's an old battleaxe of a queen in there. Ain't gonna be fond of parting with her eggs.
Birthday cake delivery for, a... Fist King?
Got a cake for the Fist King!
I have brought sweet baked consumables for the Fist King.
Heyyy, boyo! Just tryna bring the joy of cake into your life! It's for the Fist King.
Cake?! Oh hell yeah, the king is gonna twist his fist over this! Send it down!
Go on! Light the candles and give it a shove!
Shove it! Shove it hard!
Heh-heh-heh-hehhhh... Happy birthday, Fist King.
(cheers, scattered “happy birthday, boss!” “to the king!” and suchlike)

HAAAAPPY BLOODFEAST FOR YOU, IT'S YOUR BIRTHDAY TODAY||WE GOT YOU SOME GUNS, PLEASE DON'T BLOW US AWAY!||MAAAYYYY YOUR SLAUGHTER AND TORMENT AND ALL THAT YOU CRAVE||BE YOURS ON THIS DAY, AND ALL DAYS TILL THE GRAVE—
Gaaaaahahahahaha! That's what you bastards get! Nobody crosses ol' Beatrice! Ahhh, thank you kindly, dear. Come on back for a well-earned reward.
Y'know, it's funny—word's already gotten around about Beatrice's infamous explodin' cakes, and orders are shootin' through the roof over here. Guess you done me two in one there, Vault Hunter.
That's enough of them eggs! I know it sounds like a weird ingredient, but trust me! Old family secret!
You there. Help me out with somethin'?

See, I'm gonna bake me up some vengeance cake for the Flaming Fists clan! The eggs'll help the dough rise, and the gunpowder will help it, you know, explode in their faces. Hahagaha-HA! Just a little warnin'—when the oven gets hot, so do I.
Heh-heh. Looks like one of them idjits got his-self stuck in the barrel chute and gummed up the works. Which means the barrel got sent off to a side-chute. Go fish one outta there for me instead.
That should be everythin' I need for the cake. Bring 'em on back.

Now, take it on over to the Flaming Fists compound—I won't tell you how they got their name, but let's just say a swab of lard goes a long way. Anyway, tell 'em the cake is for the Fist King's birthday.
Now ring the bell and give 'em my birthday regards.
It does me good to hear the wailing cries of my enemies as they burn alive to death.
Oh! I was saving this piñata for an extra special birthday event, but I think you've earned a whack or two at it. It's all yours, Vault Hunter!
The COV over there rigged up this crazy game called the “Chute and Blow” that spits out barrels of gunpowder. Grab me one.
Y'know, them COV boys may be nuttier than an all-male dairy farm, but they sure know how to party! Mmmhm. Believe you me.
You're quite the saucy old broad, ain'tcha?
Blrgh. Please don't say things like that.
You're breaking up! Didn't hear any of that.||—Yeuch.
That would entirely defeat the purpose of a dairy farm.||—Oh.
Just get in there and show ol' Beatrice that you're, uh... good with your hands. Heh-heh.
Ugh.
Tch! Chi, chi, chi...
Ugh.
Hahahaha! Ohhoho...
